# Quality Management System (QMS) Implementation Plan

Build a comprehensive pharmaceutical QMS with a premium React frontend and a robust Node.js/Express backend. The system will handle tracking of quality checks, deviations, CAPAs, and more.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The application will consist of a separate frontend (React) and backend (Node.js). You will need to run two terminal processes: one for the frontend (`npm run dev`) and one for the backend.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend (Node.js/Express)
A new backend will be created in a `server` directory.

#### [NEW] `server/server.js`
Main entry point for the backend API.
- Express setup
- REST endpoints for each module:
    - `/api/ipq`: In-Process Quality
    - `/api/deviations`: Deviation Management
    - `/api/capa`: CAPA
    - `/api/fpq`: In-Product Quality
    - `/api/complaints`: Product Complaints
    - `/api/recalls`: Recall Management
    - `/api/aer`: Adverse Event Reporting
    - `/api/suppliers`: Supplier Management
- Shared data storage (In-memory for demo).

### Frontend (React/Vite)
Update the existing Vite project in the `QMS` subfolder.

#### [MODIFY] `QMS/src/App.jsx`
- Main layout with navigation sidebar.
- State management for active module/tab.

#### [NEW] `QMS/src/components/Dashboard.jsx`
Overview of all QMS activities with status indicators.

#### [NEW] `QMS/src/components/ModuleView.jsx`
Generic or specific views for each QMS module.

#### [MODIFY] `QMS/src/index.css`
Premium design system with modern aesthetics.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Verification of API endpoints.
- UI flow testing using the browser tool.

### Manual Verification
1. Run backend: `node server/server.js`
2. Run frontend: `npm run dev`
3. Verify all 9 modules are accessible.
